[ LAUGHTER AND APPLAUSE ]

00:07:02.560 --> 00:07:05.260
I BELIEVE IN THE IDEA OF AMERICA.

00:07:05.260 --> 00:07:08.170
I BELIEVE IN THE IDEAL OF AMERICA.

00:07:08.170 --> 00:07:10.740
COME ON, AMERICA. I KNOW WE CAN DO BETTER.

00:07:10.740 --> 00:07:12.240
I KNOW THAT YOU'RE ABLE.

00:07:12.240 --> 00:07:13.770
I'M NOT SOLANGE OR BEYONC�,

00:07:13.770 --> 00:07:15.710
BUT I DESERVE A SEAT AT THE TABLE.

00:07:15.710 --> 00:07:17.980
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:07:17.980 --> 00:07:23.420
THIS IS A MOMENT THAT WE CAN CHANGE THINGS.

00:07:23.420 --> 00:07:25.250
BUT WE GOT TO COME DOWN FROM OUR HIGH PLACE.

00:07:25.250 --> 00:07:28.320
WE GOT TO COME DOWN FROM THAT PLACE THAT MAKES US THINK

00:07:28.320 --> 00:07:30.460
THAT WE'RE RIGHT AND THE OTHER PERSON IS WRONG,

00:07:30.460 --> 00:07:31.860
AS OPPOSED TO SAYING,

00:07:31.860 --> 00:07:34.290
"THEY GOT TO THAT PLACE BECAUSE OF THE LIFE

00:07:34.290 --> 00:07:36.930
THAT THEY'VE LIVED AND THE PEOPLE THAT RAISED THEM

00:07:36.930 --> 00:07:40.130
AND THE SITUATIONS THAT FRAMED THEM."

00:07:40.130 --> 00:07:42.230
IT'S REAL QUIET, AND I KNOW THIS IS MORE LIKE A LECTURE SERIES,

00:07:42.230 --> 00:07:45.040
BUT I'M A BLACK PREACHER, SO PLEASE ALLOW YOUR INNER NEGRO

00:07:45.040 --> 00:07:47.110
TO COME OUT FOR THE NEXT 10 TO 12 MINUTES.

00:07:47.110 --> 00:07:49.410
AND YOU CAN SHOUT ME DOWN LIKE, "I KNOW THAT'S RIGHT.

00:07:49.410 --> 00:07:51.980
YOU BETTER SAY THAT. HE TALKIN' GOOD, GIRL.

00:07:51.980 --> 00:07:53.980
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:07:53.980 --> 00:08:02.790
THAT'S GOOD!"

00:08:02.790 --> 00:08:06.930
SO, WHAT DOES AMERICA LOOK LIKE? HOW DO WE HEAL?

00:08:06.930 --> 00:08:09.360
WE'VE GOT A LOT OF HEALING.

00:08:09.360 --> 00:08:10.830
I KNOW THAT WE'RE BROKEN.

00:08:10.830 --> 00:08:12.730
AND HOW CAN YOU NOT BE HURT

00:08:12.730 --> 00:08:14.500
WHEN YOU'RE IN THE AGE OF ALTERNATIVE FACTS?

00:08:14.500 --> 00:08:18.440
THAT'S LIKE SAYING, "I GOT FAT BY EATING ALTERNATIVE SNACKS."

00:08:18.440 --> 00:08:23.740
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:08:23.740 --> 00:08:24.980
I DON'T KNOW WHY YOU'RE LAUGHING.

00:08:24.980 --> 00:08:26.210
YOU KNOW THAT IT'S TRUE.

00:08:26.210 --> 00:08:28.250
AND DON'T JUDGE ME, 'CAUSE YOU GOT STUFF, TOO.

00:08:28.250 --> 00:08:31.680
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:08:31.680 --> 00:08:34.950
BUT I THINK ABOUT THE FAR RIGHT AND THE FAR LEFT,

00:08:34.950 --> 00:08:37.690
AND I'M TRYING TO FIGURE OUT, "HOW DO WE MEET IN THE MIDDLE?

00:08:37.690 --> 00:08:41.830
HOW DO WE BUILD BRIDGES OF UNDERSTANDING AND CONNECTIVITY

00:08:41.830 --> 00:08:44.200
BEYOND RACE, BEYOND GENDER,

00:08:44.200 --> 00:08:45.500
BEYOND SEXUAL ORIENTATION,

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:47.570
BEYOND RELIGIOUS PREFERENCE AND IDEOLOGY?

00:08:47.570 --> 00:08:49.070
HOW DO WE GET TO THIS PLACE?

00:08:49.070 --> 00:08:51.840
ALL OF US CAME FROM SOMEWHERE.

00:08:51.840 --> 00:08:53.840
AND SO I'M TRYING TO FIGURE OUT, "WHAT IS MY ROLE TO PLAY?"

00:08:53.840 --> 00:08:56.270
'CAUSE I GREW UP IN A LITTLE CHURCH, AND AT 7 YEARS OLD,

00:08:56.270 --> 00:08:59.510
I CONNECTED TO THE DIVINE PRESENCE OF THE MOST HIGH GOD

00:08:59.510 --> 00:09:03.050
THROUGH THIS MAN NAMED JESUS. THAT'S HOW I CONNECTED.

00:09:03.050 --> 00:09:06.050
AND MY MOTHER -- SHE DIDN'T JUST PREACH IT, SHE LIVED IT.

00:09:06.050 --> 00:09:09.020
AND I WAS LIKE, "THIS IS SOMETHING THAT CONNECTS TO ME,"

00:09:09.020 --> 00:09:10.960
BECAUSE SHE ACTUALLY LIVED IT OUT.

00:09:10.960 --> 00:09:14.160
AND IT WAS A WEIRD THING, BECAUSE MY MOTHER WAS ALWAYS

00:09:14.160 --> 00:09:17.000
THE ONE CHOCOLATE SPOT IN A SEA OF VANILLA.

00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:20.230
SHE FOUGHT TO BUILD BRIDGES AND SHE ALWAYS FOUGHT

00:09:20.230 --> 00:09:22.640
TO GIVE EVERY HUMAN BEING EQUAL VALUE.

00:09:22.640 --> 00:09:25.040
AND IN CINCINNATI IN THE '70s AND '80s,

00:09:25.040 --> 00:09:28.670
IN A VERY CONSERVATIVE AND NON-POST-RACIAL SOCIETY,

00:09:28.670 --> 00:09:31.510
SHE STOOD OUT LIKE A BEAUTIFUL SORE THUMB, SAYING THAT,

00:09:31.510 --> 00:09:33.950
"I'M NOT GOING TO ALLOW WHAT HAPPENED IN THE PAST

00:09:33.950 --> 00:09:37.680
TO DICTATE MY FUTURE." AND SHE CREATED, IN ME,

00:09:37.680 --> 00:09:40.890
A HUNGER TO BUILD BRIDGES WITH PEOPLE THAT DIDN'T LOOK LIKE ME,

00:09:40.890 --> 00:09:42.690
DIDN'T COME FROM WHERE I CAME FROM,

00:09:42.690 --> 00:09:44.320
AND DIDN'T BELIEVE WHAT I BELIEVE.

00:09:44.320 --> 00:09:46.460
AND EVERY SINGLE INDIVIDUAL

00:09:46.460 --> 00:09:49.330
THAT YOU WILL EVER SEE HAS THE SAME EQUAL VALUE.

00:09:49.330 --> 00:09:52.400
DOESN'T MEAN WE AGREE, BUT WE'RE ALL FAMILY.

00:09:52.400 --> 00:09:55.840
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

00:09:55.840 --> 00:09:57.700
SOMEBODY MAKE SOME NOISE.

00:09:57.700 --> 00:10:01.770
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE INTENSIFIES ]

00:10:01.770 --> 00:10:04.540
GREAT. I'M IN HERE SWEATING.

00:10:04.540 --> 00:10:09.080
I DONE LOST 6 POUNDS UNDER THESE HOT PRISON LIGHTS.

00:10:09.080 --> 00:10:11.050
-TAKE IT OFF! -TAKE IT OFF?

00:10:11.050 --> 00:10:12.520
DON'T DO IT, 'CAUSE I...

00:10:12.520 --> 00:10:13.590
[ BEATBOXING ]

00:10:13.590 --> 00:10:20.160
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:10:20.160 --> 00:10:24.500
I THINK ABOUT MY UPBRINGING AND I THINK ABOUT WHAT IT MEANS

00:10:24.500 --> 00:10:27.500
TO BE WHERE I'M AT RIGHT NOW, STANDING IN FRONT OF YOU.

00:10:27.500 --> 00:10:29.270
AND I'M REALLY KIND OF BLOWN AWAY,

00:10:29.270 --> 00:10:31.140
BECAUSE I SHOULDN'T BE HERE.

00:10:31.140 --> 00:10:33.140
MY MOM AND DAD DIVORCED WHEN I WAS VERY YOUNG.

00:10:33.140 --> 00:10:36.380
HE WALKED OUT THE DOOR FOR THE LAST TIME WHEN I WAS 4 1/2.

00:10:36.380 --> 00:10:39.510
I SAW HIM FOUR TIMES IN MY LIFE.

00:10:39.510 --> 00:10:40.950
BUT IT DIDN'T STOP MY MOTHER

00:10:40.950 --> 00:10:42.880
FROM DOING WHAT SHE NEEDED TO DO,

00:10:42.880 --> 00:10:46.090
WORKING FULL TIME DURING THE DAY AND GOING TO COLLEGE AT NIGHT,

00:10:46.090 --> 00:10:49.350
ENDING UP GRADUATING WITH HONORS WITH HER DEGREE IN SOCIAL WORK,

00:10:49.350 --> 00:10:51.760
AND BECOMING ONE OF THE MOST ACCOMPLISHED

00:10:51.760 --> 00:10:53.930
AFRICAN-AMERICAN WOMEN IN THE HISTORY

00:10:53.930 --> 00:10:58.400
OF THE STATE OF OHIO SOCIAL-WORK SYSTEM.

00:10:58.400 --> 00:11:00.230
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

00:11:00.230 --> 00:11:04.270
I CAME FROM A WOMAN THAT WOULD NOT GIVE UP.

00:11:04.270 --> 00:11:06.140
I'M SURE THERE WERE TIMES WHEN SHE WANTED TO,

00:11:06.140 --> 00:11:07.840
BUT THERE WAS SOMETHING ON THE INSIDE.

00:11:07.840 --> 00:11:09.240
AND EVERY MORNING AND EVERY NIGHT,

00:11:09.240 --> 00:11:11.440
I WOULD SEE HER PRAYING AND READING IN THIS WORD.

00:11:11.440 --> 00:11:13.450
AND THEN, OF COURSE, I HAD TO DO THAT, TOO.

00:11:13.450 --> 00:11:15.510
THERE WAS NO OPTION FOR ME.

00:11:15.510 --> 00:11:18.050
MY MOTHER MADE SURE THAT I WAS GOING TO BE DIFFERENT

00:11:18.050 --> 00:11:19.950
FROM THE LEGACY THAT I CAME FROM,

00:11:19.950 --> 00:11:21.620
BECAUSE, GROWING UP, PEOPLE WERE SAYING,

00:11:21.620 --> 00:11:23.420
"BE A MAN OF GOD. BE A MAN OF GOD."

00:11:23.420 --> 00:11:25.660
BUT HOW CAN YOU BE WHAT YOU'VE NEVER SEEN?

00:11:25.660 --> 00:11:28.260
Woman: PRAISE HIM!

